        "collapsible_row_abqQ6z": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "I already eat somewhat healthily. Do I actually need a blueberry powder?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Probably not. But consider this: fresh blueberries are seasonal, expensive, and expire within days. Most people eat them 2-3 times a week at best. Research on anthocyanins consistently shows that daily, consistent intake is what drives cognitive and antioxidant benefits - not occasional consumption.<br/><br/>More Green Blueberry Powder is not a replacement for a healthy diet. It is an easy way to make daily blueberry realistic, regardless of season, budget, or whether you remembered to buy them this week. One spoonful. Every day. That is the shift.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_wRYLDi": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is this safe for daily use? What about children and pregnant women?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>More Green Freeze Dried Blueberry Powder contains one ingredient: freeze-dried blueberry. No additives, preservatives, or synthetic compounds.<br/><br/>For healthy adults: safe for daily use at 3-6g per day.<br/>For children (3+): safe in smaller amounts (1-2g) mixed into food or drinks.<br/>For pregnant or breastfeeding women: blueberry is a whole food. </p><p>Always consult your doctor before adding any supplement for children or during pregnancy.<br/>For people on blood-thinning medication: blueberry contains Vitamin K. Speak to your physician if you are on anticoagulants.<br/><br/>FSSAI Licensed. Tested for purity. No synthetic inputs.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_FbCGgM": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How do I know the product is what it says it is?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>The supplement market in India has a trust problem. More Green was built to be the opposite.<br/><br/>→ FSSAI Licensed: regulated as a food product from Day 1<br/>→ Single ingredient: Freeze Dried Blueberry. The label is the truth.<br/>→ Tested for purity before it ships<br/>→ Natural colour: the purple is real. No dye added.<br/>→ No maltodextrin. No flow agents. No synthetic inputs.<br/><br/>We are a small Bengaluru brand with our names and faces on this product. We have every incentive to be honest and no incentive to cut corners.<br/><br/>Reach out to us on founders@moregreen.in</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_tnDMk3": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "There are other blueberry powders. Why More Green?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Three reasons.<br/><br/>1. Single ingredient. Most competitors use maltodextrin as the first ingredient. You are paying for filler. More Green has one ingredient: blueberry.<br/><br/>2. Freeze-dried, not spray-dried. Spray-drying uses heat, which degrades anthocyanins - the compound that makes blueberry valuable. The vibrant purple in our powder is proof of retention. Cheaper powders are often beige-brown. Ask yourself why.<br/><br/>3. Transparent. FSSAI licensed, tested for purity, label that reflects what is in the jar. No black-box manufacturing.<br/><br/>You are deciding what to put in your body every day for the next year. That decision deserves an honest answer.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
